@node pulizia "BBS cleanup menu item"
This menu item starts the message base cleanup.

In every area whose @{i}Max mess.@{ui} checkmark (which may be set from the
@{"area configuration" link WI_label_10} window) active, all the messages read which exceed
the value shown in the @{i}Max  mess.@{ui} slider (which may also be
adjusted from the @{"area configuration" link WI_label_10} window), unless they have the
@{"Keep" link GR_grp_1} checkmark active; if this is the case, they will be kept
in the message base. In addition to this, all the messages whose
@{"Delete" link GR_grp_1} checkmark is set will be deleted.

Read the @{"excess messages deletion" link cancellazione} for further information.
@endnode

@node cancellazione "Excess messages deletion"
The message base can be cleaned up in two ways:

- Manually, at any time, using the menu item @{"BBS cleanup" link pulizia}.

- Automatically, every time you quit Bomb!.

To enable automatic cleanup you must set the corresponding checkmark in the
@{"area configuration" link WI_label_10} window. The cleanup activation is based upon
hysteresis, which is used to determine how often the message base should be
cleaned up. In fact, due to Bomb!'s message base organization, the cleanup
can take some time and you could wish to avoid to perform it too often.

The @{i}Max messages hysteresis@{ui} (which may be set from the
@{"BBS configuration" link WI_label_2}) window) determines the number of excess messages which can
be held in the message base before cleanup is started.

More accurately, the program sums up the number of messages found in each
area which have the@{i}Max messages@{ui} flag active; then it evaluates the
sum of the @{i}Max messages@{ui} value of all the areas with the value of the
@{i}Max messages hysteresis@{ui} field.
If the number of messages is greater than this result, the cleanup is
started, restoring each area to the number of messages stated in its
@{i}Max mess.@{ui}.

Example:

Let's suppose we have in AMP BBS the following 4 areas:

  PVT            @{i}Max mess.@{ui} inactive (messages are never deleted)
  AMIGA          @{i}Max mess.@{ui} set to 200
  TELEMATICA     @{i}Max mess.@{ui} set to 100
  COMPRO-VENDO   @{i}Max mess.@{ui} set to 100

and the hysteresis value is 500.

Question: When does Bomb! start auto deletion?

Answer: When the total number of messages contained in areas AMIGA,
TELEMATICA and COMPRO-VENDO is greater then 200 + 100 + 100 + 500 = 900 (the
PVT area is not considered, since its @{i}Max mess.@{ui} is inactive).
@endnode

