@NODE requisiti "Required hardware/software"
- @{i}Hardware: @{ui} Bomb! should work on any Amiga with OS 2.0+. A hard
  disk is nearly indispensable.

- @{i}Software: @{ui}Bomb! requires @{"MUI" link mui} (Version 3.3) by Stefan Stuntz.
  Thanks to MUI, Bomb! is fully configurable and customizable; many
  features of Bomb! were easily implemented with the help of MUI. MUI can
  be somewhat heavy for systems with a plain 68000 or, worse, with scarce
  RAM.

  If you want to take advantage of the auto decrunching of message packets, or PGP
  encrypting/decryptinc, UUencoding and UUdecoding, of course you need the
  decrunchers, and PGP and the UUencoding/decoding programs must be
  installed.

  If you plan to use POP3, SMTP and NNTP filters, you must have a correctly
  configured and running TCP/IP stack. Bomb! has been tested in conjunction
  with AmiTCP 4.0+ and Miami (any version).

@ENDNODE

