@NODE WI_label_10 "Areas configuration"

In the left listview you can see all the areas of  the  currently  selected
BBS. You can remove an area by clicking on the Remove button after you have
selected it.

The @{i}Default values@{ui} button permits you to reset all fields relative to the
selected area to their default values; you can choose default values in the
@{"Area defaults" link default_aree} group of the global configuration window.

On the top right you can find a @{i}Max mess.@{ui} field, composed by a checkmark
and a slider; if checkmark is disabled (and slider ghosted), messages  will
never be deleted; if the checkmark is enabled, the slider allow you to
choose how many messages will be preserved on the next @{"pulizia" link pulizia}

The checkmark @{i}Learn user list@{ui} controls the behaviour of this area with
respect to user list; if checked will be extracted from every  message  the
sender name, which will be inerted in the user list; you can use this list,
later, when you want to send a message to someone (if he isn't  present  in
the list you can always type his name manually, obviously).

With the @{i}Default navigation@{ui} checkmark you can choose between 'sequential'
and 'tree' navigation.

Next you can find three string gadget with file requester button. The first
allows to choose an ASCII file containig a @{"heading" link intestazione} string.
The second allows to choose a file containing a signature. The third allows
to  choose  the taglines file. The format of this last file is explained in
the @{"Tagline file format" link fortag} section.

You can have different heading, signature and tagline files for every area.
@ENDNODE

@NODE WI_label_13 "List of messages matching a string"

In this listview you can see the list of messages matching the  string  you
were searching for.

For every message are shown:

- The number.

- 4 flags (FTSM) which, if checked, mean that the string found in the
  corresponding field of the message.
  (F=From, T=To, S=Subject, M=Message body)

  @{b}Example: @{ub}---M shows that the string was found in the message body.
           --SM shows that the string was also found in the Subject field.

- The BBS the message belongs to.

- The area the message belongs to.

- The message subject.

As usual message to be read are rendered in italic style.

To read one of the selected messages, you only need to click on it: in  the
main  window  will  show  up the text and the first matching string will be
highlited with a bold style.

From the list window you can also save or print one or more messages.
