@NODE qwkexpinfo "Other informations on qwk.exp"

    You get best results if you use qwk.exp  together  with  its  "brother"
    @{"qwk.imp " link qwkimpmain}; this is because qwk.exp needs to know some data
    that qwk.imp extracts from input packets; this is not  my  fault,  it's
    due to QWK format. If you need to use a different input filter, you
    should at least import a packet with qwk.imp, to set up environment as
    possible.

    It's IMPORTANT that archiver doesn't add any extension to packet  name;
    thi  can  be  obtained  by  specifying  "-X" flag if you use LhA or Lzx
    (well, Lzx seems not  to  recognize  this  options);  others  archivers
    should have a similar flag. If you don't do this, BBS won't accept your
    packet.

    It can be nice to suppress output from archiver (using "-q" flag if you
    use  LhA  or Lzx); if you do this, archiver won't open a window for its
    output.

